  "talk": [
    { "text": "The brahmavihāras are four ways the heart opens. " },
    { "term": "metta", "surface": "mettā" },
    { "text": " wishes beings well without condition. When mettā meets " },
    { "term": "dukkha", "surface": "dukkha" },
    { "text": ", it becomes " },
    { "term": "karuna", "surface": "karuṇā" },
    { "text": " — compassion. When it meets another's success, it becomes " },
    { "term": "mudita", "surface": "muditā" },
    { "text": " — joy that asks for nothing. And " },
    { "term": "upekkha", "surface": "upekkhā" },
    { "text": " holds all of it steadily, even when nothing can be done." }
  ],
